{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3c4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6156"},"text":"§ 6156.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Acceleration of replacement of cesium blood irradiation sources","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3c5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Goal","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The Administrator shall ensure that the goal of the covered programs is eliminating the use of blood irradiation devices in the United States that rely on cesium chloride by ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2027-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 2027","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3c6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Implementation","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"To meet the goal specified by subsection (a), the Administrator shall carry out the covered programs in a manner that—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3c7-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" is voluntary for owners of blood irradiation devices;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3c8-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" allows for the United States, subject to the review of the Administrator, to pay up to 50 percent of the per-device cost of replacing blood irradiation devices covered by the programs;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3c9-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/b/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" allows for the United States to pay up to 100 percent of the cost of removing and disposing of cesium sources retired from service by the programs; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3ca-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/b/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" replaces such devices with x-ray irradiation devices or other devices approved by the Food and Drug Administration that provide significant threat reduction as compared to cesium chloride irradiators.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3cb-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Duration","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The Administrator shall carry out the covered programs until ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2027-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 2027","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3cc-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Report","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Not later than 180 days after the date of the enactment of the John S. McCain National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2019 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232"},"text":"Public Law 115–232","children":[],"tail":"), the Administrator shall submit to the appropriate congressional committees a report on the covered programs, including—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3cd-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" identification of each cesium chloride blood irradiation device in the United States, including the number, general location, and user type;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3ce-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a plan for achieving the goal established by subsection (a);","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3cf-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/d/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a methodology for prioritizing replacement of such devices that takes into account irradiator age and prior material security initiatives;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3d0-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/d/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in consultation with the Nuclear Regulatory Commission and the Food and Drug Administration, a strategy identifying any legislative, regulatory, or other measures necessary to constrain the introduction of new cesium chloride blood irradiation devices;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3d1-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/d/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" identification of the annual funds required to meet the goal established by subsection (a); and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3d2-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/d/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a description of the disposal path for cesium chloride sources under the covered programs.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3d3-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Assessment","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The Administrator shall submit an assessment to the appropriate congressional committees by ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2023-09-20"},"text":"September 20, 2023","children":[],"tail":", of the results of the actions on the covered programs under this section, including—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3d4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/e/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the number of replacement irradiators under the covered programs;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3d5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/e/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the life-cycle costs of the programs, including personnel training, maintenance, and replacement costs for new irradiation devices;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3d6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/e/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the cost-effectiveness of the covered programs;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3d7-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/e/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" an analysis of the effectiveness of the new irradiation devices’ technology; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3d8-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/e/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a forecast of whether the Administrator will meet the goal established in subsection (a).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3d9-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/f"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"f"},"text":"(f)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Definitions","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In this section:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3da-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/f/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The term “appropriate congressional committees” means—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3db-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/f/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Committee on Appropriations, the Committee on Armed Services, and the Committee on Energy and Commerce of the House of Representatives; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3dc-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/f/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Committee on Appropriations, the Committee on Armed Services, the Committee on Energy and Natural Resources, and the Committee on Health, Education, Labor, and Pensions of the Senate.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3dd-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/f/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The term “covered programs” means the following programs of the Office of Radiological Security of the National Nuclear Security Administration:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3de-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/f/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Cesium Irradiator Replacement Program.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3df-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6156/f/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Off-Site Source Recovery Program.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idaac1e3e0-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added and amended ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/60/dC/tXXXI/s3111/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–60, div. C, title XXXI, § 3111(a)","children":[],"tail":", (d)(2)(A), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2025-12-18"},"text":"Dec. 18, 2025","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/139/1380"},"text":"139 Stat. 1380","children":[],"tail":", 1462.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idaac1e3e1-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idaac1e3e2-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idaac1e3e3-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The date of the enactment of the John S. McCain National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2019, referred to in subsec. (d), is the date of enactment of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232","children":[],"tail":", which was approved "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-08-13"},"text":"Aug. 13, 2018","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"idaac1e3e4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 6156 was renumbered ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s8267"},"text":"section 8267 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Provisions similar to those in this section were contained in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/s3141"},"text":"section 3141 of Pub. L. 115–232","children":[],"tail":", which was set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t50/s2569"},"text":"section 2569 of Title 50","children":[],"tail":", War and National Defense, prior to repeal by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/60/s3111/b/15"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–60, § 3111(b)(15)","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idaac1e3e5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2025—Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/60/s3111/d/2/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–60, § 3111(d)(2)(A)","children":[],"tail":", struck out pars. (1) and (2) headings which corresponded to the defined term in each par."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
